text:
A32 Series Power Circuit Breakers
Product Overview
NOARK Electric is proud to offer its A32 family of Power Circuit Breakers, Non-Automatic Disconnect
Switches, and accessories. Our A32 products are optimized for OEMs and are manufactured under
world-class quality systems in our ISO accredited factories. Like all NOARK products, these breakers
are designed to deliver high quality, superior performance, and outstanding value.
A32 Power Circuit Breakers are available up to 3200 amps and are capable of IC ratings up to 100kA
at 635 Volts. UL Listed and CSA Certified, the A32 family of products provide design standardization
for OEM’s no matter where they do business. A32 breakers offer a broad range of available trip
units, accessories, and communications options. They are the ideal OEM solution for low voltage
switchgear and customized power distribution assemblies used in Data Centers, Standby Power,
Industrial, Healthcare and Commercial applications.
Ratings Protection & Control Options
• 800A through 3200A • LI, LSI, or LSIG Protection
• IC ratings up to 100kA at 635V • Standard LED display
• Short-Time Withstand, 100kA at 635V • Color LCD display available
• 50 or 60 HZ operation • Optional multi-metering trip unit with
total harmonic distortion analysis and
• 3 Pole and 4 Pole designs
waveform capture
• 10,000 Operations, before maintenance (Mechanical)
• Stored energy operating mechanism
• 6000 Operations, before maintenance (Electrical)
• AC and DC rated motor operator,
• Meets ANSI C37.13, C37.16, C37.17 and C37.50
shunt trip and undervoltage release
accessories
• Arc Flash Reduction Maintenance Mode
• Zone Selective Interlocking
• RS-485 Modbus Communication
available
Approvals Design Features
• UL 1066, Low-Voltage AC and DC Power Circuit Breakers • UL/CSA field-installable accessories
• CSA C22.2 No. 31 • Rear horizontal or vertical connections
• ANSI C37.13 Low Voltage Power Circuit Breakers • Through-the-door design
• ANSI C37.16 Low Voltage Power Circuit Breakers • 3 Pole and 4 Pole designs
Ratings, Related Requirements and Applications
• OEM optimized Cassette
• ANSI C37.17 – IEEE Standard for Trip Systems
• Phase barriers (optional)
• ANSI C37.50 – Low Voltage AC Power Circuit Breakers,
• Available as Disconnect Switch (ASD32)

text:
A32 Series Power Circuit Breakers
Trip Unit Overview
A32 Trip Units offer the advanced electronic protection and control functionality
required for power distribution and feeder protection in today’s increasingly
complex power systems. The A32 trip unit’s purpose-built electronic circuits and
microprocessors measure the breaker’s electrical values against pre-set or user-
selected parameters for overload, short circuit, current unbalance, over/under
voltage, and over/under frequency. When required, a residual ground current
transformer provides sensing for ground fault protection.
In addition to the standard LS, LSI and LSIG circuit protection functions, A32
trip units can offer advanced Digital Metering, Arc Flash Reduction Mode and
Zone Selective Interlocking. Communications capability is available, ensuring
that the trip unit’s metered values and status can be transmitted to any required
monitoring or control networks.
A32 Trip Units consist of three models, each providing different levels of control, display,
diagnostics, and communications options, meeting the requirements of a wide range of end-use
applications. Each model can be ordered in one of three protection configurations.
Models: Protection Configurations:
• Model M – LED display • LI: Long Time-delay Overload, Instantaneous
Short Circuit.
• Model A – Color LCD display with a 3-phase
ammeter • LSI: Long Time-delay Overload, Short Time-delay
Short Circuit, Instantaneous Short Circuit
• Model H – Color LCD display with multi-metering
and total harmonic distortion waveform capture • LSIG: Long Time-delay Overload, Short Time-
delay Short Circuit, Instantaneous Short Circuit,
Equipment Ground Fault
Features:
• Microprocessor based true rms sensing • Available zone selective interlocking
• Discrete rotary trip setting dials • Available arc flash reduction mode
• Cause of trip LEDs • Available RS-485 communications
• Unit status LED • USB port for power & communication
• Making / breaking protection (MCR) • Service short circuit protection (HSISC)
• Ready-To-Close Indicator
